20/12/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The trial stemming from the assassination of late Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic resumed, following a month-long break.
The judges are expected to hear from witnesses who were near the shooting scene in March 2003.
A number of former Serbian government officials are due to testify as well.
Former paramilitary leader Milorad "Legija" Lukovic and a dozen other people have been charged in connection with the murder.
(Beta, B92 - 20/12/04;
AFP - 17/12/04)
